# Loads the dev-shell, then records its /nix/store closure for nix-direnv-cdi.
#
# `use flake` materialises the dev-shell (and a gcroot under .direnv) and loads
# its environment. `nix-direnv-cdi gen` then writes that shell's closure to
# .direnv/cdi/mounts.json, which the CDI hook reads at `podman run` time.
#
# Run `direnv allow` once after editing this file. A direnv reload re-runs both
# lines, so the closure stays in sync when you change dependencies.

use flake
nix-direnv-cdi gen

# Non-flakes alternative — delete the two lines above and use:
#   use nix            # loads shell.nix
#   nix-direnv-cdi gen
#
# Or, with the contrib helper sourced in ~/.config/direnv/direnvrc:
#   use flake
#   use cdi
